# Ignore host-side build outputs and dev metadata so they don't clobber
# the in-container builder stage's freshly-installed/compiled artifacts.
#
# Without this file, `COPY . .` in the Dockerfile's builder stage copies
# the host's node_modules/ (including a host-platform mediasoup-worker
# binary) on top of the container's freshly-Linux-compiled one — producing
# an image whose worker fails to spawn with `ENOEXEC`. The OLD Dockerfile
# masked this bug because the production stage's `npm ci --omit=dev`
# silently reinstalled mediasoup. The post-#1098 compile-then-copy
# architecture exposes it. See `[internal]rules/media-plane.md`
# "Docker Build Context Invariant" for the discipline.

node_modules
dist
coverage
.git
.github
.env
.env.*
*.md
docs/
*.test
*.log
.DS_Store
